neering group (SGE).\r\n					The SEG provides a continuous integration service for other the Compuses. It is designed to assist researchers in developing high quality and well tested code for\r\n					use in their work.\r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					The SGE is currently expanding the range of tools and platforms supported and is intending to include High Performance Computing (HPC) platforms,\r\n					which is an exciting and innovative opportunity. The role will also provide advice, guidance and support for those new to the service and/or new to \r\n					automated testing, allowing researchers to gain the most benefit from the service.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<u>\r\n						The duties will include:\r\n					</u>\r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					&nbsp; - Implementation of additional build nodes across a range of platforms, including links to HPC services<br>\r\n					&nbsp; - Integration of new tools and compilers within the Jenkins environment.<br>\r\n					&nbsp; - User support of the SEG including assisting new users and projects<br>\r\n					&nbsp; - Development of specialised material for supporting software testing and continuous integration<br>\r\n					&nbsp; - Responsibility for the day to day running of the service\r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					There will be opportunities to share this work with others in the wider professional community.\r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					This role will require occasional travel to other locations.\r\n				</p>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div id=\"tabs-2\" aria-labelledby=\"ui-id-2\" class=\"\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-hidden=\"false\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n				<p>\r\n					<u></u><br>\r\n					<u>\r\n						Shortlisting Criteria\r\n					</u>\r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					<em>Essential:</em>\r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					A degree in an appropriate computing or technical discipline, or demonstrate significant relevant expertise.\r\n				</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					Experience in programming languages such as Java, C, C+